caption: Good service, delicious food. However, Please update your physical menus. I saw a dish labeled as vegan(It had the green v next to it) yet when I read the ingredients it included eggs. I disregarded it and ordered the tofu fried rice instead since it was labeled as vegan and egg was not on the ingredients. Yet, when it arrived it had egg. I've since gone to the website and I noticed it is not mislabeled online, but in the physical menu it is. I would recommend updating this.
Good vegetarian options, quick service
Friendly staff and the Pho was really tasty!
Food and service was great.
Pretty darn gewd. And I'm from California where good Vietnamese food is expected.  This place was 🔥
The Pho, with chicken. Was excellent.
Best vietnamese food in STL! Staff is super friendly and the food is top notch

Wonderful food, very very friendly and helpful in helping me explore their menu. Also the staff helped me navigate back to where I was staying as I was new to the area. I am grateful and thank ful. PS their Shrimp Spring Rolls were AMAZING!!

I love this place, but the take-out I got last night was quite disappointing - the pho was way too salty, to the point of being almost inedible, and the stir-fried noodles were so greasy I had to pour off a bunch of grease that had pooled in the container.  The shrimp spring rolls were really the only thing that was up to their usual standard.  Wishing I had spent my $40 elsewhere...
Excellent service and food very attentive staff and ckean
Get soup and spring rolls... delicious!
Staff don't speak Vietnamese, the food is ok though
Staff was really friendly when explaining the menu to me! Food was delicious and fresh. Beverages also were very excellent. Menu is large and provides a great selection for diverse cravings.

Mike and his team do an amazing job! The food was incredible, and we loved being able to sit out on the patio for the fresh air and social distancing. The Pho & Steak Salad we’re probably our two favorites, but the eggrolls were also incredible! We had our two little ones with us as well, so this was also kid friendly and easy for them. Highly recommend!

Always delicious and SO fresh! Love this place! We're CRAZY about the fresh spring rolls! Wrapped in rice paper, with shrimp, greens and fresh herbs, and served with a super tasty peanut sauce. We have to get those every time. Our favorite entree is the Bo Luc Lac. The meat is always so tender and flavorful. This restaurant truly cannot be beat when it comes to delicious, reasonably priced, quality food, and top notch service. We'll continue coming rather habitually 😜. Thank you so much!!

We love this place! It's my wife's favorite 😁 We've been hitting it up more over the summer to take advantage of the patio seating and also making it a ritual with the kids to get ice cream afterwards. Owner is super nice and staff are friendly.
Outstanding place for vietnamese food. Dropped in on Mon I think. This place has a good atmosphere.
Excellent food with fresh authentic taste. I know it's not my culture but gosh do I feel like I'm in Vietnam when I taste the food. Awesome service and presentation. Very safe outdoor dining space
It's an ok place. But just not happy what I got the last time I was there.i have had better.
I love this place, though it can be a bit pricy.  The good and service are great.
Simply the top St. Louis Vietnamese style restaurant and delivery - love it !   Yummy - incredible owners too!

Tried this place out for the first time today, and was not entirely pleased... I feel like if you’re craving authentic Vietnamese cuisines, Mai Lee or Pho Grand are your best options!  When I made my order today, I was kind of shocked when the waitress asked me to spell the name of the dish that I wanted. Midway into spelling it, she cut me off to ask for the English name of the dish instead. Since it wasn’t on the online menu, I literally had to describe the dish to her, as well as my friend and cousin with their orders. I just thought that was super unprofessional, and time consuming.  Anyways, I ended up ordering Pho tac biet, and let me just say it barely had any flavor, even after I added the hoisin/Siracha sauce. I only took 5-6 bites and decided I was DONE. The broth legit tastes as if it was made from hot dog water. My cousin on the other hand, ordered Bo Kho that came out with rice mixed in. Rice??? Not going to lie, that caught us all off guard, because it’s usually served with Vietnamese baguettes. When we asked about that, they said they didn’t serve it with bread... like how disappointing is that? That’s like eating cereal with no milk. The cafe su da also had such an odd consistency, that made my throat itch. And not too long after we left, both my friend and I started having some abdominal pain... we most likely won’t be coming back again.  On the flip side, I really enjoyed the atmosphere. It was really nice, and so were the workers.

Another hidden gem restaurant in the CWE with a staff that shows professional hospitality with impeccable service providing fresh delicious cuisines in this cafe ambiance. Thanks. Try their delicious cuisines and taste something different off the beaten path
Excellent atmosphere,  good food and reasonable prices

I could seriously eat here everyday!! Not only is the quality of the food amazing but the servers and staff are super friendly and welcoming. Every time I'm town I must make a stop here. The steak cubes are my all time fav.
The best Vietnamese food in Missouri & just walking distance from STLCOP! The Bo Luc Lac, Cha Gio & Cafe su da are all must haves
Crispy spring rolls and steak cubes are my go to. Pho tai is also very tasty. Would definitely recommend trying these items
I’m all about that pho dac biet! Best in town!
Great food, better service...Little Siagon.  A true Gem in the STL food scene.
Healthy Vietnamese eating in the CWE. Would recommend the ice coffee and pastries in the morning.
Love the food and great service every time! I travel from the county to the city to hang out with friends there because of the great environment. Highly recommended!

If you haven't eaten here you should. The staff definitely treat you like a friend and the food is delicious. The food really reminds me of my family's recipes. So it really hits the nostalgia factor. I've also seen the reviews saying that the pho is plain tasting, there's a good reason for that and they do not advertise it, they don't use msg in their broth. Again, eat here if you haven't!

Amazing food and atmosphere!! My friends and I love coming here. The wait staff is super friendly and accommodating and the drinks are phenomenal. Highly recommend for anyone who’s looking for a good time with amazing food and drinks!
Love this place. Great service and amazing atmosphere, I have enjoyed my food with great city view, listening live music on patio. Definitely will come back!
Amazing food!!!
Love little Saigon! Authentic food, great location, very clean and friendly place, workers are really nice as well. The Bo luc lac and pho tai bo vien are amazing! Would recommend to everyone
I love this place! The food is amazing! My favorite thing to get here is the Pho Dac Biet.
SO GOOD! Great service, food and overall experience. Love sitting on the patio when it’s nice out. Been many times, and everything has always been delicious!

myself & my kids eat here a lot near had an issue until today. Ordered through postmates, never got my food so i called, the guy who answered the phone rushed me off the phone, in the mist of me talking  HUNG UP ON ME!!!!! saying its not his problem, its postmates .....call them.
Some of the food that u could put in your mouth

Wanted to go out and support some small buisnesses and restaurants because of the pandemic. My fiancé and I aren't the most adventurous eaters but we decided to give Vietnamese cuisine a try. We were blown away and want to thank Little Saigon for introducing us. I could eat the Pandan Honeycomb Cake all day long and their sauces, vegetables, and rice are so well done and refreshing its a new spot for us. The spring rolls are awesome too. Can't wait to go out to dinner when the restaurant is open fully after the covid-19 pandemic.

Just got Nem Nuong Cuon and Pho Tai as carry-out for a late lunch and found nirvana. Everything -- every single ingredient -- was super fresh and just plain delicious. If you're looking for yummy, healthy comfort food to help you deal with the social-distancing blues, order from here!

The restaurant was very clean and well kept. Staff was amazing and helpful. The calamari was the bomb dot com, and we really enjoyed the Pho. Happy hour prices were good. I would recommend.  In addition.. the restrooms were very clean! That’s always a plus. 🙃

The staff was nice and the restaurant was clean. The Pho soup was not very flavorful. To top it off, they charged us a 20% automatic gratuity on our bill. We were only a party of 5...a standard family with 3 kids.
Friendly staff, tasty food.
Friendly and nice place. But, foods tastes plain  and kinda over price
Amazing food in trendy central west end! Modern touch to the authentic cuisine! Exceptional service with a relax atmosphere! Most stop in if you’re in the area!
I left pretty quickly after getting my food here. First I saw a LADYBUG in my food - I told them immediately and they said they would make a new dish. Then I proceeded to find a MAGGOT.

Expensive, small portion but expensive. Probably because of the area. Friendly and helpful staff, Pho was ok, but he vegetables seemed old. Hard to find parking on street so the other option is the garage which costs. It’s not a lot but still
Amazing find... was in CWE for lunch and found this cafe by accident... very please with the flavor and quality

Best Vietnamese in StL  It can be a challenge to find good Asian food of any variety in the mid west, but this place is a gem. Easily best I’ve had in St Louis. Papaya salad is a highlight, could be in Hoi Chi Min!  Ban Xeo is great also. Can’t wait to try more of the menu.
Wonderful service! Exceptional food! Great neighborhood restaurant in the busy central west end! Must try!!

I've had lunch here a few times and I've loved the food and service every time. Staff is very friendly.  Food is beautifully presented and delicious. Staff is friendly and service prompt without feeling rushed even when I went in near the closing of the lunch shift. Highly recommend.
A must GO, so good!

Excellent food.  Always fresh, consistent, and flavorful.  For appetizers, I recommend the shrimp spring roll, calamari,  or the chicken satay. For lunch/dinner I recommend the Mi Hoanh Thanh( Wonton Egg Noodle Soup), Bo Luc Lac (Tender Steak Cubes), or the Com Ga Hainan (Ginger Rice).  They have great options for vegetarians too.
Never had a bad dish there, always start out with some fresh & fried spring rolls!
It was very good first time being there.

Went here last week for dinner with some family from out of town! Little Saigon did not disappoint! There is plenty of seating: on the patio, inside but with the windows open, at the bar, or completely inside. The bar serves delicious house cocktails and a variety of wine and beer. I tried the Saigon Slinger, it was strong and sweet, and I would get it again for sure.  The food was also amazing! I tried the Cai Xao Dao Hu, which was stir fried veggies and fried tofu served in a sauce (although I’m not sure what type) and I had it with brown rice. I cleaned the whole plate. The tofu was cooked perfectly! My uncle tried the chicken satay and pineapple fried rice which he loved. My aunt tried the dish with the ginger rice cooked in a clay pot. I tried a bite of hers and it was very light and refreshing with the ginger.  Small touches that I appreciated were the fresh flowers on the table and the lit candles. It made dinner feel very classy. We also had a very nice waiter, although I never got his name.  I would absolutely recommend eating here! The price is to be expected with the location and service they provide.
This gem impressed me as they make their own desserts homemade and all of their food is high in quality and tasty.  Their customer service is superb, love them!
Great Vietnamese, love the Pho (soup), casual atmosphere
Food was great. Nice sized portions
I went for dinner with friend to this little Saigon place. Awesome, fresh and tasty food...and about the mango margarita so strong I had to ask to add more mango juice. Thank you 👍

The restaurant had really good food and the staff was phenomenal. They seemed understaffed and still everything ran smoothly. Working in the restaurant industry myself I can appreciate good service like that.
Looks and tastes so good! We like it so much!!!!
great service and authentic food！
Love this place. Amazing atmosphere and great city dining. The food and cocktails here are amazing!

Good food and good service.  Ordered Ga Pho (chicken) one of the spices they brought me was shiracha sauce which I won't eat, unfortunately it was mixed in with the other spices that I could have added so I didn't use any of them. I do wish I could have gotten more bean sprouts but I wasn't able to explain to the young waiter what I was wanting.
Yum! So full of pho. I love you pho man. I love you.

I didn't think anything could get better  than Pho Grand but little Saigon has done it. The restaurant space is much more open and the seating isnt cramped. I was able to tuck away and lavishly enjoy my soup while peering at the book I brought. I love places that have spots where you feel like your the only one there! The staff was amazing the minute I hit the door. I was greeted with great smiles and enthusiasm. I felt like I was being welcomed into a home. I loved being called "darling" by my waiter Tony. I got the Pho Ga which was absolutely tasty (actually perfect if you Pho fan)and finished it off with their coconut cream  ice cream, SO delicious. I left feeling happy and relaxed and already planning my next girl night and hubby date there! I want to try their fried banana and honey over vanilla ice cream!
Amazing food, great atmosphere. You can really tell the chefs are passionate about what they do.
Very tasty food and friendly staff. Perfect place to have a date night or a work dinner. We will for sure be going back!Thumbs up

I have been here many times over the past few years. After today, I probably won't go there any more. The food quality has gotten worse every time, but the price gotten higher. Now average over 15 dollars for a vietnamese dish; it is very pricy comparing to other places. I ordered the fried rice. The chicken was not fresh at all, looked like plastic, tasted weird. The rice itself was very tough, like just heated after taking out from the freezer. All the vegetables in the dish taste just like those have been frozen for a long time. Why do they still exist? Unfortunately, Little Saigon is the only vietnamese restaurant around CWE. Please, someone open a new and better one soon. I like vietnamese, but I can't tolerate the food quality in this restaurant.
Food and staff were excellent
Not bad in area of St. Louis.

The food here was tasty. I had the hu tieu do bien, shrimp dumplings, cafe sua da, and banh xeo.  They were all good. The only thing was, I think the bang xeo would've been even better if the meat was sliced thinner. Also, the service was friendly.
Pho broth=6. Noodles=8. Beef balls=8. Rare steak=6. All though they have nice thick cut rare steak cuts they lacked flavor. Overall a forgettable noodle soup.
Great place for Phô, either for a date or after hitting the bars! The servers are super accommodating & the bowls are large and deliciouss. 🍜🍺
Always excellent. Quick service. Quiet atmosphere. Love this place.
Good quality and service!

Little Saigon is a quaint Vietnamese eatery just on the outskirts of the vibrant Central West End neighborhood.  From the outside, it maybe a bit easy to miss.  However, the inside has very modern, posh styling, with versatility perfect for a first date or business dinner.  I have eaten here on a few occasions and each time I found the food to be incredible.  Despite St. Louis being known for a multitude of very high quality Asian restaurants, Little Saigon is a standout. I highly recommend this place!
Amazing place.

Delicious food! We had seafood pho and chicken pho. Both fresh and flavorful, so good! Xochi and the gentleman helping her were very nice. Check out the welded sculpture to the left when you first walk in.

Wrost tasting Pho ever...
Food was delicious
Love , love , love this restaurant! Awesome food.
Very friendly staff but the Pho was pretty bland compared to other vietnamese places I've tried
Great location and service but unfortunately the pho was really bland.
The food for the most part was good, but nothing special. The calamari was super rubbery :(

Friendly staff. Nice little place with large accessible bathrooms. Cute decor. Windows face Euclid for people watching. Not a huge menu but everything we've ever had here has been very good. I love their summer rolls. The pineapple fried rice is very popular with my family. Chicken satay has a spicy kick making it even better. The noodle bowls are good and the soup bowls are too. Really you can't go wrong here. Street parking is possible off peak hours with Park Mobile. There is a public parking garage across the street in the same block.
Food was very good the service was not so great...slow and forgetful, maybe due to lunch crowd but??
Great location good food strangly limited menu
Great location in Central West End, friendly staff, and delicious food.

Very good. The friendliest ppl as well! I thoroughly enjoyed partaking in the green beans served with steak strips and the pineapple fried rice with chicken. Will definitely be visiting again in the very near future. Real recognize real you know what I’m saying though. Stay up Saigon we gone link up real soon. You absolutely must get A Vietnamese iced coffee. Ball out!!

The pho is bland compared to other places. However it was big sized and the meat balls are very good. I would suggest the beef to be sliced thinner and to make the soup more flavorful. The servers did a good job.
My favorite Vietnamese restaurant in St. Louis fresh and consistently good.
There is a great variety of food choices. The wait staff was very attentive and the atmosphere was very comfortable.  Everything we tried was delicious.
Such good food. I was blown away. Really good iced tea as well.
An excellent spot for Pho (and other amazing dishes!) In the CWE! One of our favorites.
Don't miss their "Flan"! Worth the Voyage!
I was hesitant to go because of some reviews about the soup, but I am glad that I decided to form my own opinion. The service was quick and the soup was amazing!
Service is a bit on the slower side, it's also a pain to split checks in larger groups here. Food is ok!
Tasty dishes with fresh ingredients, quickly prepared.
Pretty good food. Near the hospital with a good price point. Can't go wrong here.
Good good, quick service and reasonable prices.
Had their beef pho (noodle soup) and it was very bland, underwhelming, and below average at best.

The wait staff could be a bit friendlier considering the prices you pay. 😕 Male waiter was who I had. I ate there 8-8-17 @630ish..  The salmon was a 6 out of 10. The portion was small for $20, the bok choy was more of a garnish when I was expecting a side if it, and a small scoop of rice.. It was not worth it to me and the food was ok but not fantastic.  It was nice to be able to sit outside. 😊
Nice setting, great place to stop for lunch!
It wasn't the best beef noodle soup in town. I've tried different places, not too excited about this one.

I don't even know how to express my gratitude for these guys! My parents held a small party here, and I had been there only once before. My parents ordered a bunch of table appetizers, and David (owner I think) brought me out a special plate with chicken satay since my parents forgot I was allergic to everything they ordered 🙄 How he remembered that from a visit 3 weeks prior, I have no idea, but color me impressed. They took care of our party, with us never wanting for anything. Every single dish was incredible. The lemondrop martinis are tasty (and dangerous!), and my ginger chicken had actual fresh ginger ground on top. Awesome. A definite recommendation if you find yourself in the Central West End.
This is NOT real pho.  They do not even have tripe or tendon, and their meat combo is a joke.  Quality isn't bad, buy white-washed for a very specific crowd that doesn't know any better
The food is flavorful. I highly recommend the crispy spring rolls and shaken beef with jasmine rice. Our server was great!
Good service,  good food
Consistently my favorite place to eat near my house in CWE over the last year. It's just always delicious. Tyler is easily the best waiter I've had in St. Louis!

This place never disappoints!  Food is always super fresh, very tasty, and reasonably priced. I've been here 25+ times and it continues to get better.  Friendly family owned joint that is now a go-to staple for us.

The food is fine, it is not bad, it is not the best, but it is fine.  I do not care for the fact that they do not turn on the air-conditioning inside when it is super hot outside. I'm sorry but when it is horrible hot outside and you walk in and it is just as hot inside as outside that is not a comfortable experience. If I wanted that, I would sit outside. The service is kinda lousy. They do not come back to the table and you may wait and wait if they come at all.  I have left in the past without ordering and myself and one other table were present.

First time having Vietnamese food and boy was it wonderful. I got the shaking beef and my wife got a beef bowl. The serving sizes were bigger than we expected!  The shaking beef was wonderful,and likely a new favorite of mine. My wife enjoyed her beef bowl so much she made she to get the remainder to go.  I highly recommend this place! Was cheaper than we expected as well.
Great place for a delicious lunch of dinner. Amazing food with quick and friendly service. Some of my favorite calamari I've ever had. Affordable for the quality of food.
Food was just ok. But the service was great.

The food was delicious! I ate here for lunch and had the chicken curry. The service was good. The location is a little hard to find, but the pictures posted of it helped me to find it. It is on the east side of Euclid Ave, near the corner of Lacleade and Euclid.
Good Vietnamese option
Nice food . Good price. But parking near by can be a problm

This restaurant has a sleek and modern interior. The food was very delicious. Two entrees were enough to split between 3 people. I believe the quality and portions match the prices. I would definitely come back.
Authentic. Decent service and good variety of options. Try the spring rolls.

Fresh, friendly, and fantastic! Before moving to STL, I was lucky enough to have eaten here several times. When I decided to move to STL, I already had a favorite restaurant. I no longer live in the CWE, so I don't eat here as often, but it's still in my top 5.  The menu is lovely and the staff helpful. They give great recommendations and are incredibly attentive.
Staff is friendly.  Great atmosphere great food
Try the Shaking Beef and the Summer Rolls.  There is a full-service bar, too.  Menu and prices are the same for lunch and dinner.
I had the beef noodle soup (pho) for lunch. It wasn't very authentic and $10 (very affordable but maybe slightly more than usual) , but it wasn't bad, and the service was friendly and fast.

Authentic Vietnamese food at decent prices. Restaurant, including bathroom, is very clean. Since the weather was so pleasant, we sat outside on the sidewalk patio. We ordered the crispy spring rolls and meatball and beef soup. Both were served promptly. Spring rolls were very crispy and filled with fresh savory ingredients. Meatball and beef soup was huge and chock full of meat and noodles. It came with cilantro, jalapeño and bean sprouts along with hoisin and sriracha.  Highly recommend!
Pretty good Vietnamese good. The service is quick and efficient.

Regarding St. Louis restaurant, Little Saigon is a Big Deal.  I don't necessarily mean it has a fan base that rivals the Cards, but I mean it has almost everything you could want from an eating establishment, leaving little to be desired.  Delicious food, great service, decent prices, and an excellent sidewalk setup make Little Saigon a great way to experience Vietnamese food and the Central West End.
I try something new each time I go, and never been disappointed yet.

It was magical!! Very intimate and personal with a brilliant flare!!!

I ate here on a business trip. The wait staff was knowledgeable about what was gluten free. I especially appreciated the fact that each of the wait staff took the time to check in on me. Great place to eat. Hope I can stop in again soon.
Incredible. Their Pho Tai was the best I've ever had, the service was excellent, and the waiter chased after me because I forgot my card at the table. I will definitely be back.

Great little place, the portions are decent (not huge like a previous reviewer suggested), the servers are polite, the atmosphere is bright and clean, and the overall experience was very positive.  The fried tofu with shitake mushrooms and veggies was nicely done, as were the vegetarian egg rolls. Definitely would return.
Just visited for the first time. I will be back.
Yummy soups! Large portions. And the service was fairly quick, even with a party of 10 people. I've chosen this place for my birthday lunch outing twice since I like it so much.

St. Louis has a great selection of Asian restaurants, but Little Saigon differentiates itself with its linen table cloth atmosphere. Great service, menu that includes both Vietnamese and Chinese entrees, and excellent martinis.

These guys have the BEST chicken noodle soup and Vietnamese coffee. Their price are VERY cheap in my opinion. $7 for a HUGE soup with extra. $10 for this huge chicken plate.  The main thing that keeps us coming back is the quality and taste of the food.  Just amazing.
